column8: I recently had the pleasure of taking the "Moscow Highlights Tour," and it was an absolutely incredible experience from start to finish! Our journey began at the iconic Red Square and the Kremlin, where seeing St. Basil's Cathedral up close was a dream come true. The Moscow Metro stations, each an underground palace, were a surprising highlight. Strolling down historic Arbat Street, visiting the magnificent Bolshoi Theatre, and ending with a leisurely walk through Gorky Park provided a perfect blend of history, culture, and relaxation. Our guide, Elena, was exceptional, bringing Moscow's rich history to life with her impressive knowledge and engaging storytelling. This well-organized tour was a fantastic way to see the best of Moscow in a single day, and I highly recommend it to anyone visiting the Russian capital.
